# Stack Conventions — Halo

## Next.js (App Router)

- All routes under `app/` — no `pages/` directory
- API routes under `app/api/` as Route Handlers (`route.ts`)
- Use Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when needed (event handlers, hooks)
- No hardcoded secrets — all keys via environment variables

## Supabase

- Schema defined via migrations, not the dashboard UI
- Use the Supabase JS client (`@supabase/supabase-js`) server-side in API routes
- Row Level Security (RLS) on all tables — even for a demo build
- Seed demo data via a script (`scripts/seed.ts`), not manual inserts

## Claude API

- Use the `@anthropic-ai/sdk` package
- Always define a typed response schema and use structured outputs — never parse raw strings
- Validate the structured output at the API boundary before passing to the frontend
- Keep system prompts in `lib/prompts/` as typed constants, not inline strings
- Use `claude-sonnet-4-6` as the default model

## TypeScript

- Strict mode on — no `any` types
- Define shared types in `lib/types.ts`
- Zod for runtime validation at API boundaries

## Environment Variables

Required in `.env.local`:
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
```

Never commit `.env.local`. Confirm `.gitignore` includes it before first commit.

## Deployment

- Deploy target: Vercel
- Set all env vars in Vercel dashboard before deploying
- Smoke-test the deployed URL — not just local — before the demo
